        <p style="font-size:18px; line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>🇹🇼 Taiwanese revokes visa of an influencer over pro-Beijing material</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
            Taiwan has ordered Chinese influencer Liu to leave by March 24 or face deportation. This comes in light of videos she posted supporting China’s <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-03-2025-h1-1-forceful-unification-with-taiwan?source=website" target="_blank">forceful unification with Taiwan</a>. The National Immigration Agency revoked her visa, stating her remarks undermined Taiwan’s sovereignty. Liu, known online as "Yaya," moved to Taiwan after marrying a local man.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5"> 
            She frequently refers to Taiwan as “Taiwan province,” which is taboo in Taiwan. She has made claims that unification by force may be necessary. Amid backlash, Liu insisted she was promoting understanding. However, officials condemned her comments, saying free speech does not justify calling for invasion. Her removal reflects rising tensions as President Lai Ching-te tightens regulations to counter China’s influence in Taiwan.
          </p>
          </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.2;">
          <strong>🇬🇧 UN judge found guilty of domestic servitude</strong> 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; filter:blur(5px);">
          Lydia Mugambe, a Ugandan high court judge and UN judicial official, has been convicted in the UK for forcing a young woman into domestic servitude. Prosecutors argued that Mugambe <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-03-2025-h2-2-exploited-her-power?source=website" target="_blank">exploited her power</a> by bringing the victim to the UK under pretenses. She prevented her from securing paid employment and coerced her into unpaid work as a maid and childcare provider.
          </p>
       
          </mj-text>
